STEPS TO SETUP THE ENVIRONMENT FOR OPENCV:-

STEP1: 

DOWNLOAD THE ANACONDA DISTRIBUTION FROM THE GIVEN LINK: 
https://www.anaconda.com/download/


STEP2:

INSTALL THE ANACONDA DISTRIBUTION.

chmod +x Anaconda3-5.0.1-Linux-x86_64.sh

./Anaconda3-5.0.1-Linux-x86_64.sh 


STEP3:

CREATING THE VIRTUAL ENVIRONMENT FOR PYTHON3.5 PACKAGES

conda create -n py35 python=3.5 anaconda

# To activate this environment, use:
# > source activate py35
#
# To deactivate an active environment, use:
# > source deactivate

source activate py35
conda install -c conda-forge opencv

INSTALLING THE TENSORFLOW IS OPTIONAL
# conda install -c conda-forge tensorflow

python -m ipykernel install --user --name py35


STEP4:

CHECK WHETHER ALL THE INSTALLED PACKAGES ARE WORKING PROPERLY.
